HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 300
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
COMMENDATIONS: Commends the valedictorians of the 2026 graduating class of
Chalmette High School
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend the valedictorians of the 2026 graduating class of Chalmette High School.
3 WHEREAS, valedictorians are the graduating students who earn the highest GPA,
4 and they represent the apogee of scholastic success; and
5 WHEREAS, valedictorian status requires world-class consistency and near perfect
6 grades across all subjects over the entirety of high school; and
7 WHEREAS, beyond consummate academics, valedictorians exhibit relentless work
8 ethic in extracurricular leadership, and they are traditionally tasked with delivering
9 graduation day speeches to inspire their fellow graduates toward future greatness; and
10 WHEREAS, the valedictorians of the Chalmette High School graduating class of
11 2026 are Celine Bioc, Maya Dufrene, Lillian Lai, Christian Miller, Jackson Nunez,
12 Ella Tabora, Samantha Thornton, and Evan Ye; and
13 WHEREAS, these young men and women are deserving of recognition for their
14 incredible achievement.
15 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
16 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend the valedictorians of the 2026 graduating
17 class of Chalmette High School and does hereby extend sincerest wishes that they continue
18 their excellent work and always strive for greatness.
